quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  12,5,"He said, “O my child, do not relate your vision to your brothers, lest they plot a plot against you; indeed, Satan is an evident enemy to man."
  12,6,"And thus your Lord will choose you and teach you of the interpretation of dreams and perfect His blessing upon you and upon Jacob’s folk, as He perfected it before upon both of your forefathers Abraham and Isaac; indeed, your Lord is All-Knowing, All-Wise."
  12,7,"Very truly, there have been signs{1}in Joseph and his brothers for the askers.",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Ibn Kathir read it as: “Very truly, there has been a sign…”
  12,8,"Recall when they said, “Joseph and his brother are certainly dearer to our father than we are, although we are a<i>(whole) </i>band. Most surely, our father is in evident misguidance."
  12,9,"“Kill Joseph or throw him somewhere in the land, and your father‘s attention will be yours, then afterwards you become righteous people.”"
  12,10,"One{1}of them said, “Do not kill Joseph, but cast him into the invisible cavity{2}of the unlined well—some travelers may pick him up—if you must do something.”",footnotes:1:[Literally ‘a speaker of them’.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…invisible cavities…”]
